Assignment Overview
The Async Weather Tracker
The Async Weather Tracker is a hands-on lab assignment designed to help students understand asynchronous programming in JavaScript and how JavaScript behaves at runtime.
In this lab, students will build a weather information system using Vanilla JavaScript and the Fetch API, focusing on async/await, promises, error handling, event loop behavior, and Local Storage—without using any frameworks or external libraries.
This assignment simulates real-world API interaction and helps students debug and analyze execution order using browser developer tools.
